# Per-stage config for scripts/run-loop-news.sh — copy this file to
# scripts/run-loop-news.env (gitignored) and uncomment/edit what you want to change.
# run-loop-news.sh auto-sources scripts/run-loop-news.env if it exists.
#
# Precedence (highest wins): CLI flag  >  this file / exported env var  >  built-in default.
# CLI flags (--search-model, --model, etc. — see `run-loop-news.sh --help`) are for a
# one-off run; this file is for a standing local default without exporting anything.

# ── Search stage (Skill A · fetch-loop-news) ──────────────────────────────────
# Model: an alias (sonnet|opus|fable) or a full model id (e.g. claude-sonnet-5).
# LOOP_SEARCH_MODEL=sonnet

# Effort: low | medium | high | xhigh | max.
# LOOP_SEARCH_EFFORT=high

# Max turns for the search session.
# LOOP_SEARCH_MAX_TURNS=40

# --max-budget-usd tripwire (see note below) for the search stage.
# LOOP_SEARCH_BUDGET_USD=30

# ── Integrate stage (Skill B · integrate-loop-news) ───────────────────────────
# LOOP_INTEGRATE_MODEL=sonnet
# LOOP_INTEGRATE_EFFORT=high
# LOOP_INTEGRATE_MAX_TURNS=60
# LOOP_INTEGRATE_BUDGET_USD=20

# ── Note on *_BUDGET_USD under a Claude subscription (Pro/Max) ────────────────
# This is NOT a real dollar cost — you're not billed per token. It's a script-side
# tripwire computed from API list-price-equivalent token usage, meant only to stop a
# genuinely runaway/looping session. Set it generously; it shouldn't trip on a normal
# thorough run. On budget-exceeded the wrapper stops immediately (never retries — the
# same session would just hit the same wall again).
